---
cloud_id: "your-cloud-id-here"
site_url: "https://your-org.atlassian.net"
---

# Atlassian Plugin Settings

Configure this file with your Atlassian workspace details.

## How to find your cloud_id

Run this in a terminal (requires the Atlassian MCP server to be configured):

```
Ask Claude: "What is my Atlassian cloud ID?"
```

Claude will call `getAccessibleAtlassianResources` and show you the ID.
Copy it into the `cloud_id` field above.

## Setup

1. Copy this file to `.claude/private-atlassian.local.md` (without the `.example` suffix)
2. Fill in `cloud_id` and `site_url`
3. The `.local.md` file is gitignored and will not be committed

## Example

```yaml
---
cloud_id: "a1b2c3d4-1234-5678-abcd-ef0123456789"
site_url: "https://acme.atlassian.net"
---
```
